The paper introduces a Bayesian nonparametric prior on the joint space of infinite directed acyclic graphs (DAGs) and orders, which is a topic that falls under machine learning and probabilistic modeling. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.ST (Statistics). The paper also discusses the usefulness of the proposed model in learning the structure of deep generative sigmoid networks and convolutional neural networks, which are topics that fall under information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SI).
